<item>
            <title>[NET-402] BufferedReader used for control channel, which does not follow the standard</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-402</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;BufferedReader is used for wrapping the control channel, and uses its readLine() for getting responses from the server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The IMAP, NNTP, POP3 and SMTP protocols require CRLF at the end of lines, but Bufferedreader#readLine() also allows bare CR and LF terminators, which could potentially be included in a server reply.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12503463">NET-402</key>
            <summary>BufferedReader used for control channel, which does not follow the standard</summary>
